{"word":"H7799 - שׁוּשַׁן - shûwshan - shoo-shan' - Lily","slug":"H7799","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שׁוּשַׁן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shûwshan"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shoo-shan'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Lily"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D5;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E0;&#x05BC;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05DF;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D5;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05DF;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05DF; - shu&#x0302;shan  sho&#x0302;sha&#x0302;n  sho&#x0302;sha&#x0302;n  sho&#x0302;shanna&#x0302;h</b> - <i>shoo-shan' (2,3) sho-shawn' sho-shan-naw'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H7797\">H7797</a>; a <i>lily</i> (from its <i>whiteness</i>), as a flower or architectural ornament; also a (straight) <i>trumpet</i> (from the <i>tubular</i> shape): - lily, Shoshannim."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7791\">H7791</a>, <a href=\"#/H7793\">H7793</a>, <a href=\"#/H7794\">H7794</a>, <a href=\"#/H7800\">H7800</a>, <a href=\"#/H7802\">H7802</a>, <a href=\"#/H7803\">H7803</a>, <a href=\"#/H8284\">H8284</a>, <a href=\"#/H8364\">H8364</a>"}]}